    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A type of late Roman amphora that feature a tapered body with the maximum diameter occurring at the shoulder and a height from 44 to 64cm, rim diameter of 4.5 to 11cm, maximum body diameter of 28.4 to 39cm and upper part height of 16.4 to 33cm.</Note_Text>
